<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-17T12:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-17T12:36:00-05:00" n="1243" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1243">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.63/411</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Fletcher</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-17T11:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 17, 1917, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>24. Your telegram March 15, 6 p.m. Minister of Fomento appreciates
                            difficulties American mine owners will have in complying with decree in
                            the time allowed and will take up the whole mining question very soon
                            with the First Chief who is now in the Capital. Indications are that an
                            extension will be granted. Translation of the decree referred to sent
                            you in last Wednesday’s pouch.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>